9 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING EDUCATION LAWS TO LIMIT THE STATE
10 PROMOTION OF TEACHER ATTENDANCE AT MEETINGS OF TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS; PROHIBITING
11 PUPIL-INSTRUCTION-RELATED DAYS FROM BEING USED FOR ATTENDING STATE MEETINGS OF
12 TEACHER ORGANIZATIONS INCLUDING POLITICAL OR ORGANIZED LABOR ACTIVITY; REMOVING THE
13 MANDATE THAT TRUSTEES CLOSE SCHOOLS FOR THE ANNUAL MEETINGS OF TEACHER
14 ORGANIZATIONS; ENSURING THAT PUPIL-INSTRUCTION-RELATED DAYS AND TRUSTEES'
15 PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT PLANS ALIGN WITH THE STANDARDS OF THE BOARD OF PUBLIC
16 EDUCATION; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-1-304 AND 20-4-304, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE
17 DATE.”
18
19 WHEREAS, pupil-instruction-related days are supported with state and local tax dollars; and
20 WHEREAS, recent professional development opportunities for teachers utilizing pupil-instruction-
21 related days included political activity and unnecessarily divisive partisan content.
22
23 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
24
25 Section 1. Section 20-1-304, MCA, is amended to read:
26 "20-1-304. Pupil-instruction-related day. A pupil-instruction-related day is a day of teacher activities
27 devoted to improving the quality of instruction in alignment with the standards for professional development
28 adopted by the board of public education. The activities may include but are not limited to inservice training,
